node.title: Barred Owl
node.description: I've been hoping/trying to photograph an owl in the wild for some time. I finally had the opportunity to shoot this barred owl at Cades Cove last week. Little did I know it would allow me (and others) to approach within 15 yards! What an awe-inspiring experience. More shots of the National Park to come.

node.title: Lily Shoals
node.description: So I made the drive early Saturday morning to West Blocton to check out the Cahaba lilies and cross another item off the photo bucket list.  The sunrise conditions were not ideal (cloudy and rain) but I was nonetheless taken in by the beauty of the place.  The Cahaba lilies (or Shoal lilies) bloom between mid May and mid June each year.  If you live in AL and have not had a chance to view this awesome wonder, do yourself a favor!  I will definitely be back.
